{"title_page": "Tacana language", "text_new": "{{redirect|Tacana|the Mesoamerican volcano|Volc\u00e1n Tacan\u00e1|the Peruvian region|Tacna Region}}\n{{Infobox language\n| name = Tacana\n| nativename = \n| states = [[Bolivia]]\n| region = [[La Paz Department (Bolivia)]]\n| ethnicity = 5,100 (2004)<ref name=e18/>\n| speakers = 1,800\n| date = 2004\n| ref = e18\n| familycolor = American\n| fam1 = [[Tacanan languages|Tacanan]]\n| fam2 = Araona\u2013Tacanan\n| fam3 = Cavinena\u2013Tacana\n| fam4 = Tacana Proper\n| iso3 = tna\n| glotto = taca1256\n| glottorefname = Tacana\n}}\n\n'''Tacana''' is a Western [[Tacanan languages|Tacanan]] language spoken by some 1,800 [[Tacana people]] in [[Bolivia]] out of an ethnic population of 5,000. They live in the forest along the [[Beni River|Beni]] and [[Madre de Dios River|Madre de Dios]] rivers in the north of [[La Paz Department (Bolivia)|La Paz Department]]. Numerous dialects, now extinct, have been attributed to Tacana:  Ayaychuna, Babayana, Chiliuvo, Chivamona, Idiama (Ixiama), Pamaino, Pasaramona, Saparuna, Siliama, Tumupasa (Maracani, \"Tupamasa\"), Uchupiamona, Yabaypura, and Yubamona (Mason 1950).\n\n==External links==\n{{Reflist}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100819194552/http://lingweb.eva.mpg.de/ids/ Tacana dictionary online from IDS] (select simple or advanced browsing)\n*[https://ids.clld.org/contributions/276 Tacana] ([[Intercontinental Dictionary Series]])\n\n{{Languages of Bolivia}}\n{{Pano-Tacanan languages}}\n\n[[Category:Languages of Bolivia]]\n[[Category:Tacanan languages]]\n\n\n{{indigenousAmerican-lang-stub}}\n{{Bolivia-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{redirect|Tacana|the Mesoamerican volcano|Volc\u00e1n Tacan\u00e1|the Peruvian region|Tacna Region}}\n{{Infobox language\n| name = Tacana\n| nativename = \n| states = [[Bolivia]]\n| region = [[La Paz Department (Bolivia)]]\n| ethnicity = 5,100 (2004)<ref name=e18/>\n| speakers = 1,800\n| date = 2004\n| ref = e18\n| familycolor = American\n| fam1 = [[Tacanan languages|Tacanan]]\n| fam2 = Araona\u2013Tacanan\n| fam3 = Cavinena\u2013Tacana\n| fam4 = Tacana Proper\n| iso3 = tna\n| glotto = taca1256\n| glottorefname = Tacana\n}}\n\n'''Tacana''' is a Western [[Tacanan languages|Tacanan]] language spoken by some 1,800 [[Tacana people]] in [[Bolivia]] out of an ethnic population of 5,000. They live in the forest along the [[Beni River|Beni]] and [[Madre de Dios River|Madre de Dios]] rivers.  Numerous dialects, now extinct, have been attributed to Tacana:  Ayaychuna, Babayana, Chiliuvo, Chivamona, Idiama (Ixiama), Pamaino, Pasaramona, Saparuna, Siliama, Tumupasa (Maracani, \"Tupamasa\"), Uchupiamona, Yabaypura, and Yubamona (Mason 1950).\n\n==External links==\n{{Reflist}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100819194552/http://lingweb.eva.mpg.de/ids/ Tacana dictionary online from IDS] (select simple or advanced browsing)\n*[https://ids.clld.org/contributions/276 Tacana] ([[Intercontinental Dictionary Series]])\n\n{{Languages of Bolivia}}\n{{Pano-Tacanan languages}}\n\n[[Category:Languages of Bolivia]]\n[[Category:Tacanan languages]]\n\n\n{{indigenousAmerican-lang-stub}}\n{{Bolivia-stub}}\n", "name_user": "AEdwards100", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added department name to geographical location in text.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tacana_language"}
{"title_page": "Utkela Airstrip", "text_new": "{{Infobox airport\n| name         = Utkela Airstrip\n| nativename   = \n| nativename-a =\n| nativename-r =\n| image        =Utkela Air Odisha.jpg\n| image-width  =\n| caption      =\n| IATA         =\n| ICAO         = VEUK\n| type         = Public\n| owner        = [[Government of Odisha]]\n| operator     =\n| city-served  = [[Bhawanipatna]]\n| location     = [[Kesinga]], [[Kalahandi district]], [[Odisha]]\n| elevation-f  = 685\n| elevation-m  = 210\n| coordinates  = {{coord|20|05|52|N|083|11|00|E|region:IN|display=inline,title}}\n| pushpin_map = India Odisha#India\n| pushpin_mapsize =\n| pushpin_map_alt =\n| pushpin_map_caption = Location in Odisha\n| pushpin_relief =\n| pushpin_image =\n| pushpin_label = VEUK\n| pushpin_label_position =\n| website      =\n| metric-elev  =\n| metric-rwy   =\n| r1-number    = 04/22\n| r1-length-f  = 3020\n| r1-length-m  = 920\n| r1-surface   = [[Asphalt]]\n| r2-number    =\n| r2-length-f  =\n| r2-length-m  =\n| r2-surface   =\n| stat-year    =\n| stat1-header =\n| stat1-data   =\n| stat2-header =\n| stat2-data   =\n| footnotes    =\n}}\n'''Utkela Airstrip''' {{airport codes|VEUK}} is owned by the [[Government of Odisha]] located at Utkela 20&nbsp;km from [[Bhawanipatna]] in the [[Kalahandi district]] & [[Kesinga]]  of [[Odisha]], India.\n\nUtkela Airstrip (VEUK) is scheduled to be operational with daily flights to state capital [[Bhubaneshwar]] and [[Raipur]] in the coming month of September by private air service provider [[Air Odisha]] under [[UDAN]] scheme by Ministry of Civil Aviation, Govt. of India.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/economy/logistics/43-airports-to-get-flights-under-regional-air-connectivity-scheme-minister/article9607388.ece|title=Regional connectivity gets wings; five airlines get to fly 128 routes}}</ref>\n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ourairports.com/countries/IN/OR/airports.html |title=List of airports in Odisha, India (excluding heliports a