aire and the Instruction of 1767 in the English Text of 1768\". Cambridge University Press, (England), (1931), Reprint (1971).\n* {{Cite book |first=NAM |last=Rodger |title=Command of the Ocean: A Naval History of Britain, 1649\u20131815 |year=2005 |isbn=978-0-393-06050-8 |publisher=W.W. Norton & Company |ref=harv |url=https://archive.org/details/commandofoceanna00rodg }}\n* {{cite book |last=Rounding |first=Virginia |title=Catherine the Great: Love, Sex and Power |year=2006 |publisher=Hutchinson |location=London |isbn=978-0-09-179992-2 |ref=harv}}\n{{refend}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book|last=Alexander|first=John T.|title=Catherine the Great: Life and Legend|location=New York|publisher=[[Oxford University Press]]|year=1988|isbn=978-0-19-505236-7|ref=harv|url=https://archive.org/details/catherinegreatli0000alex}}\n* Bilbasov Vasily A. [https://web.archive.org/web/20190331083958/https://new.runivers.ru/lib/book4351/ ''History of Catherine the Great'']. Berlin: Publishing Frederick Gottgeyner, 1900. At [[Runivers.ru]] in [[DjVu]] and PDF formats\n* Bogdanovich Modest I. [https://web.archive.org/web/20190331085456/https://new.runivers.ru/lib/book3157/10069/ ''Russian army in the age of the Empress Catherine II'']. Saint Petersburg: Printing office of the Department of inheritance, 1873. At [[Runivers.ru]] in [[DjVu]] and [[PDF]] formats\n* Brickner Alexander Gustavovich. [https://web.archive.org/web/20190331083958/https://new.runivers.ru/lib/book4358/ ''History of Catherine the Great'']. Saint Petersburg: Typography of A. Suvorin, 1885. At [[Runivers.ru]] in [[DjVu]] and PDF formats\n* [[Vincent Cronin|Cronin, Vincent]]. ''Catherine, Empress of All the Russias''. London: Collins, 1978 (hardcover, {{ISBN|0-00-216119-2}}); 1996 (paperback, {{ISBN|1-86046-091-7}})\n* Dixon, Simon. ''Catherine the Great (Profiles in Power)''. Harlow, UK: Longman, 2001 (paperback, {{ISBN|0-582-09803-3}})\n* Herman, Eleanor. ''Sex With the Queen''. New York: [[Harper