20626020247/http://staff.gps.edu:80/mines/Age%20of%20Absol%20-%20Enlightend%20Despots.htm |date=26 June 2012 |title=The Enlightened Despots }}\n* {{in lang|ru}} [http://russia-today.narod.ru/past/gen_app/ekat2.htm Family tree of the ancestors of Catherine the Great]\n* {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110825023603/http://www.douglassmith.info/28/love-and-conquest.html |date=25 August 2011 |title=Douglas Smith, ''Love and Conquest: Personal Correspondence of Catherine the Great and Prince Grigory Potemkin'' }}\n* http://www.alexanderpalace.org/palace/Catherine.html\n* {{Cite EB1911|wstitle=Catherine II. |short=x}}\n* {{Cite NIE|wstitle=Catharine II.|year=1905 |short=x}}\n* {{YouTube|OkMy0f4SSGw|Romanovs. The fifth film. Peter III; Catherine II}} \u2013 Historical reconstruction \"The Romanovs\". StarMedia. Babich-Design (Russia, 2013)\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-hou|[[House of Romanov]]|2 May|1729|17 November|1796|[[House of Ascania|House of Anhalt]]}}\n{{S-reg|}}\n{{S-bef|before=[[Peter III of Russia|Peter III]]}}\n{{S-ttl|title=[[Emperor of Russia|Empress of Russia]]|years=9 July 1762 \u2013 17 November 1796}}\n{{S-aft|after=[[Paul I of Russia|Paul I]]}}\n{{S-roy|ru}}\n{{S-break}}\n{{S-vac|last=[[Catherine I of Russia|Martha Skowro\u0144ska]]}}\n{{S-ttl|title=[[Empress consort of Russia]]|years=5 January 1762 \u2013 9 July 1762}}\n{{S-vac|next=[[Maria Feodorovna (Sophie Dorothea of W\u00fcrttemberg)|Sophie Dorothea of W\u00fcrttemberg]]}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Russian emperors}}\n{{Age of Enlightenment}}\n{{Russian grand duchesses by marriage}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n\n[[Category:Catherine the Great| ]]<!--leave the empty space as standard-->\n[[Category:Russian empresses consorts]]\n[[Category:1729 births]]\n[[Category:1796 deaths]]\n[[Category:18th-century Russian monarchs]]\n[[Category:18th-century Russian women]]\n[[Category:18th-century women rulers]]\n[[Category:18th-century Russian people]]\n[[Category:Burials at Peter 